  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The general aim of the present study is to test a cell therapy with third-party allogeneic
      ex-vivo expanded MSCs as a strategy to induce tolerance in liver transplant recipients. MSCs
      will be prepared accordingly to established protocols , starting from diagnostic samples of
      bone marrow aspirates (2-5 mL) or using the remnants in the bag and filter at the end of the
      bone marrow infusions. From these samples, MSCs will be expanded in GMP approved facilities
      and used for the present study in patients undergoing liver transplantation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
